cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the optimization problem of selecting numerical quantities to clean in order to fact-check claims based on such data. The problem involves complex, non-linear functions over data, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves the exploration of alternative definitions of what "matters the most" in fact-checking, which could fall under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Database (cs.DB) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses potential applications beyond fact-checking, which could relate to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category.
